@CalmCaterpillar Well speaking as a straight bloke I have no problem with gay people. Live and let live etc....But I dont want to see them, interact with them or have them in my world as I am straight. Its not part of my little corner of Eden so to speak. However I would never harm, ridicule or be mean to a gay person as that is wrong and I accept that they have had a lot of grief like this over the years. Its not something I have anything to do with.

What I object to though is changing a straight or non sexual character to gay / lesbian or female and so on to make a point. To stick two fingers up to the audience and get in your face about it. That is just stupid and obnoxious behaviour and it will do their cause no good. None at all.

And that was my problem with Whitaker and Gatwa. I used to like RTD for bringing the show back in 2005 and doing such a good job to keep it Doctor Who and bring in a new audience. And now I utterly despise him for what he has done. I dont watch gay content / characters as I cant relate...I am straight. The same way I would not expect a gay person to be able to relate to straight couples etc. It is a bit of a problem for some it would seem...

